All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AttackMove
    AttackMoves are Moves which deal damage.
    ButtonClass
    Defines the different buttons available in the game.
    Character
    The Character is a creature in the game.
    Chatbot
    The Chatbot receives an input, and sends an output according to the input.
    CSVHandler
    The CSVHandler is used to read and store data in various .csv files.
    DataPacket
    The DataPacket is used to move data across different States.
    DefenseMove
    AttackMoves are Moves which block damage.
    DesktopLauncher
    DesktopLauncher to launch PokeGo
    EndGameState
    The EndGameState is displayed at the end of the game.
    Error
    Error enum defining available errors in the game.
    Font
    Defines the available fonts in the game.
    GameAnimation
    GameAnimation is a wrapper object used to render animations.
    GameAudioManager
    The GameAudioManager manages all music and sound in the game.
    GameButton
    GameButton is used to represent a clickable button.
    GameCheckbox
    GameCheckbox is used to represent a checkbox.
    GameCircle
    GameCircle is used to represent a rendered circle.
    GameErrorWidget
    Custom error widget built using GameTextWidget.
    GameInputField
    GameInputField is used to represent an input box.
    GamePhase
    Defines the different types of Phases available in GameState.
    GamePhaseManager
    The GamePhaseManager controls different Phases in the GameState.
    GameRectangle
    GameRectangle is used to represent a rendered rectangle.
    GameRoundTimer
    The GameRoundTimer object represents the timer in the GameState.
    GameShapeGroup
    Classes that inherit from GameShapeGroup uses LibGDX's ShapeRenderer to draw them.
    GameSprite
    GameSprite is a wrapper object used to render sprites.
    GameSpriteGroup
    Classes that inherit from GameSpriteGroup uses LibGDX's SpriteBatch to draw them.
    GameStartState
    The GameStartState is displayed after the PreGameState.
    GameState
    The GameState is displayed after the GameStartState.
    GameStateManager
    The GameStateManager controls the different States to be displayed onto the screen.
    GameText
    GameText represents text that is rendered by LibGDX's engine.
    GameTextWidget
    GameTextWidget represents a text box.
    HelpState
    The HelpState contains a Chatbot object.
    ICollides
    This interface defines a set of methods for objects that can be collided against animations.
    IMovable
    This interface defines a set of methods for any movable object in the game.
    MenuState
    The MenuState displays the main menu of the game.
    Move
    Defines the base class for a Move.
    MoveClass
    MoveClass specifies the types of moves available.
    Phase
    Each Phase represents a checkpoint in the GameState where the logic changes.
    PhasePacket
    The PhasePacket is used to pass data around different game phases.
    Player
    The Player represents the players that are currently playing the game.
    PlayerNumber
    Defines the possible Players in the game.
    PlayerUI
    The PlayerUI object represents a collection of Player UI elements to be displayed in GameState.
    PlayerWinner
    Defines the possible outcomes of the game.
    PokeGo
    The main game class.
    PreGameState
    The PreGameState displays the game start page.
    RoundDisplayFaintedPhase
    The Phase which displays whose Character has fainted.
    RoundDisplayMovesPhase
    The Phase which displays animations according to Moves used by respective Characters.
    RoundDisplayNextCharPhase
    The Phase which updates the Player's Character.
    RoundEndPhase
    The Phase triggered at the end of each round.
    RoundLowerHpPhase
    The Phase which lowers the HP of each Character, after calculating the amount of damage to be received for the current turn.
    RoundStartPhase
    The Phase which receive inputs from both Players.
    RoundTextMovesPhase
    The Phase which updates GameTextWidget according to what move each Character has used.
    ScoreboardState
    The ScoreboardState displays the scoreboard.
    SettingsState
    The SettingsState displays the settings menu.
    State
    A State represents a different checkpoint in the game.
    TimerUI
    TimerUI represents the timer object's UI in the middle of the screen.
    TitleState
    The TitleState is displayed at the start of the game.
    Type
    Type specifies the types available to each Move and Character.
    Utility
    Collection of misc functions to be used around the whole project.
